config ADI_SRAM_MMAP
	bool "Aarch64 MMAP driver for ADI onchip SRAM"
	depends on SRAM
	depends on ARM64 || COMPILE_TEST
	default ARCH_ADRV906X
	help
	  This option enables the memory mapping (mmap) driver for Analog
	  Devices (ADI) on-chip SRAM on ARM64 platforms. This driver allows
	  user-space applications to directly access the on-chip SRAM through
	  memory-mapped I/O, which is useful for high-performance data transfer
	  and low-latency applications.

	  Say Y here if you need user-space access to ADI on-chip SRAM.
	  If unsure, say N.

